line_1: "If such thy wishes, say what power restrains?
line_2: " O! force the bliss which ignorance disdains;

line_1: The Daemons of the mine restrains,
line_2: Tho' he with hundred gates and chains

line_1: And circling Stream your Hand restrains;
line_2: And well explore the bubbling Veins:

line_1: Winter a-while each growing herb restrains,
line_2: And locks all nature in his icy chains;

line_1: That unclaim'd wealth no property restrains;
line_2: And realize each godly act she feigns.

line_1: Warns him or prompts, approves him or restrains,
line_2: As reason, or as passion, takes the reins.

line_1: Supports the Good, the Bad his Pow'r restrains;
line_2: With most judicious Policy he Reigns,

line_1: When the proud Steed shall know, why Man restrains
line_2: His fiery course, or drives him o'er the plains;

line_1: Each strengthens Reason, and Self-love restrains.
The Muse each joyous thought restrains,
line_2: But not o'er bright Aonian plains,

line_1: Offend not him whom modesty restrains
line_2: From repartee, with jokes that he disdains,
